data.title: Burnt Flavorless Food
data.text: My husband and I ordered take out from Golden Star tonight; we ordered the Sesame Chicken combo, the Sweet & Sour Chicken combo, and an order of vegetable lo mein. The only good thing about our order was the Sesame Chicken; sweet and crispy like it should be. The fried rice in the combo plates was bland, and it was burnt so it gave off a very bitter taste. The egg rolls tasted like feet, and the sweet and sour sauce tasted old. The vegetable lo mein also had a burnt bitter taste, and the vegetables didn't taste fresh. The fortune cookies were also stale. We aren't picky people or world class foodies, but for $27 you should expect fresh food. Overall, I don't think we will return.

data.title: Our favorite for takeout
data.text: We often call Golden Star when we're at a loss for what to eat for dinner.  They always get the order right, the portions are big, and the food is always hot, good, and quick.

data.title: Run-of-the-mill takeout
data.text: No place really to sit and it - this place is built for take-out.  Nothing so far seems spectacular - pretty run of the mill Chinese food.  A bit greasy.
